## Express Standards

- Use `Router` instances to group related routes; mount them in `app.ts`
- Validate request bodies and params with a schema library (Zod, Joi) before processing
- Use typed request/response via `Request<Params, ResBody, ReqBody, Query>` generics
- Handle errors in a centralized error middleware; never `res.send(err)` inline
- Use `next(err)` to propagate errors to the error handler
- Keep route handlers thin: delegate business logic to service functions
- Return consistent JSON shapes: `{ data, error, meta }` pattern
